\f0\b \cf4 \strokec4 abstract
\f1\b0 \cf2 \strokec2   \cf4 \strokec4 =\cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 "ABSTRACTThe ventricular\'96subventricular zone (V\uc0\u8208 SVZ), lining the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                lateral walls of the lateral ventricles, is a major neurogenic\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                region in the adult brain of many mammals. This study\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                investigates the structural organization and cellular composition\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                of the V\uc0\u8208 SVZ in the juvenile swine brain (3\'965 months), providing\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                novel insights into neuroblast migration in gyrencephalic\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                species. Using immunohistochemistry combined with transmission\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                and scanning electron microscopy, we redefined the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                cytoarchitecture of the swine V\uc0\u8208 SVZ, identifying four distinct\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                cellular layers. Layer 1 consists of a pseudostratified\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                epithelium of glial fibrillary acidic protein\uc0\u8208 positive ependymal\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                cells, whose cilia and microvilli extend into the ventricular\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                lumen, frequently surrounding supraependymal axons. Beneath it,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                layer 2 is composed of astrocytic and radial glia processes and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                contains occasional clusters of doublecortin (DCX)\uc0\u8208 positive cells\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                with prominent microtubules and elongated cytoplasm, indicative\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                of a migratory phenotype. Layer 3 is further subdivided into a\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                low\uc0\u8208 cell\u8208 density sublayer 3a, enriched with myelinated axons and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                scattered DCX+ clusters, and a high\uc0\u8208 cell\u8208 density sublayer 3b,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                characterized by large groups of DCX+ migratory cells. In\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                sagittal sections, these cells form long chains oriented parallel\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                to the ventricular surface. Neuroblasts emerging from the dorsal\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                V\uc0\u8208 SVZ migrate caudorostrally through the rostral migratory stream\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                toward the olfactory bulb. The layered organization of the swine\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                V\uc0\u8208 SVZ resembles that of humans, where DCX+ chains persist up to\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                18 months of age, positioning the swine as a valuable model for\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                investigating postnatal plasticity and neurogenic potential in\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                gyrencephalic brains. The persistence of immature neurons in the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                V\uc0\u8208 SVZ of gyrencephalic mammals, including infant humans,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                underscores the relevance of this region for neurogenesis and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4                plasticity in large\uc0\u8208 brained species.",\cf2 \strokec2 \
  
