\f1\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 =\cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 "In animal tissues, several cell types migrate along blood vessels,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               raising the possibility that blood flow influences cell migration.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Here, we show that blood flow promotes the migration of new\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               olfactory-bulb neurons in the adult brain. Neuronal migration is\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               facilitated by blood flow, leading to accumulation of new neurons\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               near blood vessels with abundant blood flow. Blood flow inhibition\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               attenuates blood vessel-guided neuronal migration, suggesting that\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               blood contains factors beneficial to neuronal migration. We found\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               that ghrelin, which is increased in blood by hunger, directly\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               influences neuronal migration. Ghrelin signaling promotes somal\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               translocation by activating actin cytoskeleton contraction at the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               rear of the cell soma. New neurons mature in the olfactory bulb\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               and contribute to the olfactory function for sensing odorants from\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               food. Finally, we show that neuronal migration is increased by\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               calorie restriction, and that ghrelin signaling is involved in the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               process. This study suggests that blood flow promotes neuronal\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               migration through blood-derived ghrelin signaling in the adult\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               brain, which could be one of the mechanisms that improve the\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               olfactory function for food-seeking behavior during starvation.",\cf2 \strokec2 \
  
