\f1\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 =\cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 "Centrosomes are orbited by centriolar satellites, dynamic\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               multiprotein assemblies nucleated by Pericentriolar material 1\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               (PCM1). To study the requirement for centriolar satellites, we\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               generated mice lacking PCM1, a crucial component of satellites.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Pcm1-/- mice display partially penetrant perinatal lethality with\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               survivors exhibiting hydrocephalus, oligospermia, and cerebellar\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               hypoplasia, and variably expressive phenotypes such as\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               hydronephrosis. As many of these phenotypes have been observed in\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               human ciliopathies and satellites are implicated in cilia biology,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               we investigated whether cilia were affected. PCM1 was dispensable\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               for ciliogenesis in many cell types, whereas Pcm1-/- multiciliated\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               ependymal cells and human PCM1-/- retinal pigmented epithelial 1\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               (RPE1) cells showed reduced ciliogenesis. PCM1-/- RPE1 cells\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               displayed reduced docking of the mother centriole to the ciliary\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               vesicle and removal of CP110 and CEP97 from the distal mother\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               centriole, indicating compromised early ciliogenesis. Similarly,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Pcm1-/- ependymal cells exhibited reduced removal of CP110 from\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               basal bodies in vivo. We propose that PCM1 and centriolar\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               satellites facilitate efficient trafficking of proteins to and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               from centrioles, including the departure of CP110 and CEP97 to\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               initiate ciliogenesis, and that the threshold to trigger\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               ciliogenesis differs between cell types.",\cf2 \strokec2 \
  
