\f1\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 =\cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 "Adult neurogenesis persists in mammals in the neurogenic zones,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               where newborn neurons are incorporated into preexisting circuits\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               to preserve and improve learning and memory tasks. Relevant\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               structural elements of the neurogenic niches include the family of\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               cell adhesion molecules (CAMs), which participate in signal\cf2 \strokec2 \
