\cf4 \strokec4               CSF flow. E cells display two forms of planar cell polarity (PCP):\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               rotational polarity of individual cilium and translational\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               polarity (asymmetric positioning of cilia in the apical area). The\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               orientation of individual E cells varies according to their\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               location in the ventricular wall (location-specific PCP). It has\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               been hypothesized that hydrodynamic forces on the apical surface\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               of radial glia cells (RGCs), the embryonic precursors of E cells,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               could guide location-specific PCP in the ventricular epithelium.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               However, the detection mechanisms for these hydrodynamic forces\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               have not been identified. Here, we show that the mechanosensory\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               proteins polycystic kidney disease 1 (Pkd1) and Pkd2 are present\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               in primary cilia of RGCs. Ablation of Pkd1 or Pkd2 in\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Nestin-Cre;Pkd1(flox/flox) or Nestin-Cre;Pkd2(flox/flox) mice,\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               affected PCP development in RGCs and E cells. Early shear forces\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               on the ventricular epithelium may activate Pkd1 and Pkd2 in\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               primary cilia of RGCs to properly polarize RGCs and E cells.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Consistently, Pkd1, Pkd2, or primary cilia on RGCs were required\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               for the proper asymmetric localization of the PCP protein Vangl2\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               in E cells' apical area. Analyses of single- and\cf2 \strokec2 \
