\f1\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 =\cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 "Neural stem cells (B1 astrocytes; NSCs) in the adult\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               ventricular-subventricular-zone (V-SVZ) originate in the embryo.\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Surprisingly, recent work has shown that B1 cells remain largely\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               quiescent. They are reactivated postnatally to function as primary\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               progenitors for neurons destined for the olfactory bulb and some\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               corpus callosum oligodendrocytes. The cellular and molecular\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               properties of quiescent B1 cells remain unknown. Here we found\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               that a subpopulation of B1 cells has a unique nuclear envelope\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               invagination specialization similar to envelope-limited chromatin\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               sheets (ELCS), reported in certain lymphocytes and some cancer\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               cells. Using molecular markers, [3H]thymidine birth-dating, and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               Ara-C, we found that B1 cells with ELCS correspond to quiescent\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               NSCs. ELCS begin forming in embryonic radial glia cells and\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               represent a specific nuclear compartment containing particular\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               epigenetic modifications and telomeres. These results reveal a\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               unique nuclear compartment in quiescent NSCs, which is useful for\cf2 \strokec2 \
\cf4 \strokec4               identifying these primary progenitors and study their gene\cf2 \strokec2 \
